
                            About application
                            ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

1. General information
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  This software is a R-circuit sizing application.
  There are these calculations:
  - Bridged T-section attenuator
  - Current divider
  - Delta-Y conversion
  - L-section attenuator (a)
  - L-section attenuator (b)
  - L-section impedance converter
  - Multiplier resistor for voltmeter
  - Pi-section attenuator
  - Serial and paralell equivalent resistance
  - Shunt resistor for ammeter
  - Shunt resistor from Cu wire
  - Symmetric bridged T-section attenuator
  - Symmetric cross L-section attenuator
  - Symmetric L-section attenuator (a)
  - Symmetric L-section attenuator (b)
  - Symmetric T-section attenuator
  - T-section attenuator
  - Voltage divider
  - Wheatstone-bridge
  - Y-Delta conversion

  This is a software, which does not cost money (maybe you must pay for use
Internet).  The lope conditions is the acceptance and observance of the European
Union Public Licence.
   
   OS support: FreeBSD, Linux and Windows.
   Language support: English and Hungarian.

2. Installer packages
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
a. for FreeBSD
   r-circuits-0.4.1-FreeBSD-Port.shar   port package
   r-circuits-0.4.1.txz                 binary package

b. for Linux
   r-circuits-0.4.1-1.i586.rpm          binary package
   r-circuits-0.4.1-i586-1.txz          binary package
   r-circuits-0.4.1-i586.bin            installer programme
   r-circuits-0.4.1-i586.tar.gz         binary package
   r-circuits-0.4.1.x86.package         binary package
   r-circuits_0.4.1-1_i386.deb          binary package

c. for Windows
   r-circuits-0.4.1-win32.exe           installer application
   r-circuits-0.4.1-win32.msi           binary package
   r-circuits-0.4.1-win32.zip           binary package

d. source code
   r-circuits-0.4.1.tar.gz              source package

3. Settings
~~~~~~~~~~~
  On Linux and FreeBSD use 'LANG' environment variable to set language of the
application. (English: en_US, Hungarian: hu_HU)

